    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "The `spiral_data` function allows us to create a dataset with as many classes as we want. The function has parameters to choose the number of classes and the number of points/observations per class in the resulting non-linear dataset. \n",
        "\n",
        "If you trace from the center, you can determine all $3$ classes separately, but this is a very challenging problem for a machine learning classifier to solve. Adding color to the chart makes this more clear:"
